  <title>University of South Pacific looks to expand Tuvalu campus</title>
  <content>
The University of the South Pacific is looking to expand its campus in Tuvalu in future.
At the moment distance education over a broadband internet connection links students in Funafuti with classes at the main campus in Suva, Fiji.
The USP's Tuvalu Campus Director, Rosiana Lagi, tells Bruce Hill that the use of online education there is working very well and could be a model for other small island countries in need of advanced education services.
